@bebomac5 There is a black bourgeoisie that has participated with power to help keep us in stasis. They get away with it because many people, wrongfully, assume blacks are naturally progressive due to civil rights. The truth is, they can act just like bigoted/racists white supremacists, neoliberals and fascists. There are also many religious fundamentalist among us.

We see it with corrupt legislators in the CBC like Hakeem Jefferies and Clyburn. We see the backing of corporate and neoliberal ideologies with Obama and Oprah. We see the authoritarian side in policing with the Terry Nichols murder.

It would be criminal if West didn't point this out. And; it's either ignorance or outright lying if people think he doesn't critique the system.

@SplishSplashdash Correct! There are black socialists like myself, those who are ok with Democratic Neoliberalism, corporatists and even fascists.

We get lumped in as one group. It's time to actually expose who is maintaining the desires of a system that has been against us for centuries.

It doesn't matter if a black face is president, head of the military or a CEO. If that person maintains the same system that keeps us in stasis; it's just window dressing. They might as well hire a corrupt, anti-progressive white person and darken their skin with makeup. There is no difference.
